  <div class="comment-content">
    <span rel="sioc:reply_of" resource="/articles/2014/08/Amazon-v-Hatchette-Everyone-Wrong-Me" class="rdf-meta"></span><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden view-mode-full"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>The "one-click" patent litigation occurred in 1999, not 2009<a class="see-footnote" id="footnoteref1_go47ec2" title="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1-Click#Patent" href="#footnote1_go47ec2">1</a>. After the PR fiasco that occurred, Bezos had a change of heart regarding the patent system<a class="see-footnote" id="footnoteref2_p0t2m7o" title="http://www.oreillynet.com/pub/a/oreilly/news/amazon_patents.html" href="#footnote2_p0t2m7o">2</a><a class="see-footnote" id="footnoteref3_2ibh30m" title="http://www.oreillynet.com/pub/a/oreilly/news/patent_archive.html" href="#footnote3_2ibh30m">3</a>. I can't find a reference for it, but Amazon has not used any patents offensively in over 10 years. </p>
<ul class="footnotes"><li class="footnote" id="footnote1_go47ec2"><a class="footnote-label" href="#footnoteref1_go47ec2">1.</a> <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1-Click#Patent">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1-Click#Patent</a></li>
<li class="footnote" id="footnote2_p0t2m7o"><a class="footnote-label" href="#footnoteref2_p0t2m7o">2.</a> <a href="http://www.oreillynet.com/pub/a/oreilly/news/amazon_patents.html">http://www.oreillynet.com/pub/a/oreilly/news/amazon_patents.html</a></li>
<li class="footnote" id="footnote3_2ibh30m"><a class="footnote-label" href="#footnoteref3_2ibh30m">3.</a> <a href="http://www.oreillynet.com/pub/a/oreilly/news/patent_archive.html">http://www.oreillynet.com/pub/a/oreilly/news/patent_archive.html</a></li>
